pos_mean_info_list.mean: 竞争的；比赛的；求胜心切的

word_mean_info__list.difference: 指为战胜或击败对手进行不懈努力，强调拼搏。也可指口头上进行有对立情绪或严重分歧的争论。
指在两方或多方的竞争或比赛中，谁都想战胜或比得上对手。
指为争夺土地、阵地、权力或荣誉等而展开的竞争。
普通用词，含义广泛。既可指体育活动等活动中争取优胜的相互竞争，也可指为了自己的利益与他人竞争。

word_group.brief_definition: 在...竞争；参与...的竞争；参加...比赛

bilingual.source: I have to compete with my classmates at school.
bilingual.target: 我在学校必须和同学竞争。

bilingual.source: You shouldn't compete with your classmates to get better grades.
bilingual.target: 你不应该为了取得更好的成绩而与同学竞争。

bilingual.source: Others are practicing sports so that they can compete and win.
bilingual.target: 其他人正在练习运动，以便他们可以竞争并获胜。

bilingual.source: Oh, you shouldn't compete with your classmates to get better grades.
bilingual.target: 哦，你不应该和同学竞争以取得更好的成绩。

bilingual.source: The two companies compete in the market.
bilingual.target: 这两家公司在市场上竞争。

bilingual.source: He likes to compete in various sports.
bilingual.target: 他喜欢在各种体育活动中竞争。

bilingual.source: The rams compete fiercely during the mating season.
bilingual.target: 公羊在交配季节竞争激烈。

bilingual.source: We must strive to compete to win the game.
bilingual.target: 我们必须努力竞争，才能赢得这场比赛。

list.abstract: compete（英 [kəmˈpiːt]，美[kəmˈpiːt），英语单词，作动词为竞争、角逐、比赛、参赛、能匹敌、能对抗。例句有“We compete against market transitions , not competitors.（我们与市场转型竞争，而不是竞争对手。）” 相关近义词有contest、war、cope。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, perfect accessory. I couldn't compete.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这种完美的装备，我可没法竞争。

yingyinNormal.en: I can't compete against $120 million payroll with $38 million. We're not gonna compete with these teams that have big budgets.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我无法用三千八百万跟一亿两千万的球队竞争。那些球队预算太多，我们无法与他们抗衡。

yingyinNormal.en: Well done, Dr Watson. How useful you are. Do you have a suspicion we're being made to compete?
yingyinNormal.zh: 做得好，华生医生，你真是有用。你不觉得我们是在被操纵相互竞争吗？

yingyinNormal.en: If you expect to compete with the other teams at this school, you've got a lot to learn. Sergeant, explain the game.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要想与学校里，其他的战队竞争，你们还有很长的路要走。中士，解释规则。

yingyinNormal.en: Max, Han said no, and we need that cappuccino maker for our shop if we're ever gonna compete with the Starbucks around the corner.
yingyinNormal.zh: Max Han不答应，我们必须要有卡布奇诺咖啡机，否则就没法和街角的星巴克竞争。

yingyinNormal.en: Over the past five years we've worked hard to open new markets for our businesses and to help them compete on a level playing field in those markets.
yingyinNormal.zh: 过去5年时间里，我们努力为企业打开新的市场，帮助他们在这些地方取得竞争力。

yingyinNormal.en: He suggested that if they just leave self-interested traders to compete with one another, markets are guided to positive outcomes as if by an invisible hand.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他认为如果让这些以自我利益为主的生意人相互竞争，市场就会自然导向正面的结果，就像有只隐形的手在控制一样。

yingyinNormal.en: Uh, you have to be in a fraternity to compete.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你必须代表兄弟会才能参赛。

yingyinNormal.en: Now all you need to do is find enough members to compete.
Yes, sir. You will train to compete as a team against other teams.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是 长官，你们将被编列成队与其他战队对战。

yingyinNormal.en: Which is another way of saying he doesn't have the nerve to compete. You scared?
yingyinNormal.zh: 意思也就是他没有胆量来较量。你害怕吗？

yingyinNormal.en: He wanted to tell me he's gonna compete in some ultimate fighting competition thingy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他要参加一个什么终极格斗比赛。

yingyinNormal.en: We're the last company standing between them and total energy dominance. And we can no longer compete.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我司是唯一一间阻挡非榭能源公司垄断能源，不过我司以无抵抗之力。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, M. You can't really tell me that one man in the field can compete with all of this, running around out there with his license to kill.
yingyinNormal.zh: 拜托，M，你不会真的觉得区区一个特工能和这一切相提并论吧，凭一张杀人执照就能打遍天下吗。

yingyinNormal.en: And I suppose in the beginning we were strangers, who didn't know much about the other and sometimes we did compete for the shower and there were times when we did intrude on each other's privacy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想在最初我们是陌生人，不认识对方，有时还抢洗澡的时间，也有侵犯对方隐私的时候。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

n. 竞争对手；竞争者；参赛者；比赛者
adj. 竞争的；竞争性的；可与…匹敌的；好竞争的；有竞争心的；有竞争力的

word_family.mean: v. 竞争；角逐；比赛；参赛；能匹敌；能对抗

sense_info_list.en: strive to gain or win something by defeating or establishing superiority over others who are trying to do the same

examination_example.sentence: The rule "limited states' ability to seek long-term prosperity and has prevented market participants from <highlight>competing</highlight> on an even playing field."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这条规则“限制了国家寻求长期繁荣的能力，并阻止了市场参与者在一个公平的竞争环境中竞争。”

examination_example.sentence: However, during that course I realized I was not good enough in this area to <highlight>compete</highlight> with other creative personalities in the future.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 然而，在那个课程中，我意识到我在这个领域还不够好，无法在未来与其他有创造力的人竞争。

examination_example.sentence: The interaction and confrontation between shared and <highlight>competing</highlight> beliefs involved transforms an individual's discovery claim into the community's credible discovery.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 共同看法和竞争的观点会相互作用和碰撞，把个人的科学发现变成科学界的可信发现。

sense_info_list.en: take part in a race or competition

指为战胜或击败对手进行不懈努力，强调拼搏。也可指口头上进行有对立情绪或严重分歧的争论。
